<p>I'm trying to split a string <code>email</code> that contains HTML content into 2 parts, one before <code>&lt;div class=\"gmail_signature\"&gt;</code> and one after.</p>  <p>EDIT: Here's a sample of what's in <code>email</code>: <code>My email is here&lt;div class=\"gmail_quote\"&gt;and my signature&lt;/div&gt;</code></p>  <p>So I'd like to have <code>My email is here</code> and <code>&lt;div class=\"gmail_quote\"&gt;and my signature&lt;/div&gt;</code> separately.</p>  <p>Using <code>email.index('&lt;div class=\"gmail_signature\"&gt;')</code> returns nil, because of the <code>\"</code>. The same issue happens with <code>gsub</code>.</p>  <p>What's the best way to deal with this? Thanks!</p>